* To start off working with the scripts execute the command 'sh Scripts.sh' on the command line (console)
* To make changes to the configuration parameters, please edit the file present in the folder 'conf'
* The folders captures and logs contain the logs and captures generated by the scripts when they are run. These are captured automatically and put in those folders.
* Everytime the script is run different folders are created in those directories. Can be clearly understood when run the scripts.
* To stop the script at any point in time of its execution, please press Ctrl + c

